reviews.text:
A typical public sector bank. Customer preference always comes second after bank employee preference. I have had an account here since 2015. The services have improved in a major way since that time but it still lags in comparison to a private bank. The bank offers all the typical services of a public sector bank such as savings account, current account, various loans, etc. However, like almost every PSB, the process of availing those services is very lengthy and time consuming.
Few points -

Staff behaviour: The staff in 2015 was the most pathetic one I ever came across even when compared to that of SBI at that time. The deputy manager at that timewas so slow that I can figuratively compare him wiith a sloth and then too, the sloth would have won wrt the speed of doing work. However, the staff behaviour has substantially changed now-a-days and the gap has abridged compared to that of a private bank. After the staff completely changed in the branch after 2015, there had been two deputy managers since and both of them were at par in terms of dedication to their work and the quality of their work. They both complained about the immense amount of work pressure on them, but never compromised with their service quality. However, given the strict guidelines by the RBI, a strong private sector bank will always outweigh a public bank due to their focus on competitiveness and customer satisfaction. I therefore believe that if all other costs remain the same, why not choose a private bank?

Accessibility: It is situated near education department's office, although, reaching here is a little bit tricky if one doesn't use Google maps. However, it is very near to the Raipur ring road.

Not Disabled friendly: The office as well as the parking is not at all disabled friendly. There is no ramp available, plus the parking surface is uneven and doesn't have a separate parking space for the disabled.

Parking: Very small space in front of the bank is available for parking which is insufficient. Though the sidewalk tiles have been placed but the surface is uneven.

Additionally, the app of the bank is also very slow, unresponsive and it malfunctions many a times.

Overall, I would not recommend anyone to open an account in UCO bank if they have an option of any other bank.
